# Local Backend Context

Read `docs/claude/backend.md` for full reference before modifying backend-related code.

## Quick Reference

**Architecture:** Docker Compose on Windows 11 (12-core i7) at `C:\gpc-cres-backend\docker-compose.yml`. FastAPI gateway (:8000), Martin tiles (:3000), PostgreSQL `entitlement_os` (560K parcels, deals, orgs, PostGIS), Qdrant (vector search). Single Cloudflare Tunnel with remotely-managed ingress.

**Public URLs:**
- `api.gallagherpropco.com` → gateway:8000 (data/tools)
- `tiles.gallagherpropco.com` → martin:3000 (vector tiles)

**Auth:** Bearer token (`GATEWAY_API_KEY`), constant-time comparison. All endpoints except `/health` require auth.

**Two DB pools in `main.py`:**
- `db_pool` (`DATABASE_URL`) → property DB (parcels, geometry, screening, stats)
- `app_db_pool` (`APPLICATION_DATABASE_URL`) → application DB (deals, orgs, runs)

**Endpoint groups (20 total):**
- `/health` — no auth, health check
- `/deals` GET/POST/PATCH — application DB, org-scoped via `X-Org-Id`
- `/tiles/{z}/{x}/{y}.pbf` — Martin proxy, 24h cache
- `/tools/parcel.lookup`, `/tools/parcel.bbox` — agent tool endpoints
- `/api/parcels/search`, `/api/parcels/{id}`, `/api/parcels/{id}/geometry` — parcel API
- `/tools/screen.{flood,soils,wetlands,epa,traffic,ldeq,full}` — 7 screening endpoints
- `/api/stats` — database statistics

**Vercel env vars:** `LOCAL_API_URL` (https://api.gallagherpropco.com), `LOCAL_API_KEY` (GATEWAY_API_KEY value).

**Key files:** `infra/local-api/main.py` (gateway), `packages/openai/src/tools/propertyDbTools.ts` (agent tools), `infra/sql/property-db-rpc-functions.sql` (RPC definitions).

## Skill-Aware Editing

When editing backend-facing API or integration code for this repo, first check the relevant skill in `skills/`:

- `skills/parcel-ops/SKILL.md` for parcel and geometry execution logic.
- `skills/data-extraction/SKILL.md` for ingestion/fetch normalization expectations.
- `skills/entitlement-os/SKILL.md` for entitlement workflow context.

Use `Use when` / `Don't use when` routing from each skill to avoid cross-domain changes.
Maintain default security posture: deny-by-default network access unless a workflow-specific allowlist explicitly requires more.

**Maintenance rule:** When adding/removing endpoints in `main.py`, update `docs/claude/backend.md` endpoint inventory.
